-- Cole In Line to Make 100th England Appearance in Brazil Match
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-01-31T15:06:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-31/cole-in-line-to-make-100th-england-appearance-in-brazil-match.html
Ashley Cole  may make his 100th
appearance for the England soccer team after being included in
the squad for next week’s exhibition match against Brazil.  Cole was among the 24-man squad named today by manager Roy
Hodgson for the Feb. 6 game at Wembley Stadium in London. The
Chelsea defender would be the seventh England player to reach
the milestone, after captain Steven Gerrard played his 100th
game in Sweden in November.   Manchester United defender Chris Smalling has been recalled
to the squad for the first time in a year. Manchester City’s Joe
Hart and Birmingham’s Jack Butland are the only goalkeepers,
with Norwich’s John Ruddy and Celtic’s Fraser Forster both
injured.   ENGLAND SQUAD:
GOAKLKEEPERS: Jack Butland, Joe Hart.
DEFENDERS: Leighton Baines, Gary Cahill, Ashley Cole, Phil
Jagielka, Glen Johnson, Joleon Lescott, Chris Smalling, Kyle
Walker.
MIDFIELDERS: Michael Carrick, Tom Cleverley,  Steven Gerrard ,
 Frank Lampard , Aaron Lennon, James Milner, Leon Osman, Alex
Oxlade-Chamberlain, Jack Wilshere.
FORWARDS: Jermain Defoe, Wayne Rooney, Daniel Sturridge, Theo
Walcott, Danny Welbeeck.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
